name: Wired Fence
description: Barb Wire: Joseph Farwell Glidden  was the inventor of the modern barbed wire that was described as:   "It takes no room, exhausts no soil, shades no vegetation, is proof against high winds, makes no snowdrifts, and is both durable and cheap." Besides ranchers, railroads were large purchasers of barbed wire so that cattle did not stray onto their tracks.
